DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGgraphmacros.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

Context("Numeric");


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(3,7,2);
$b = random(2,8,2);
$i = random(2,4,1);
$c = $i*$b;
$m = -$b/$a;
$j = random(4,6,1);
$x = $j*$b;
$y = $a*$j-$i;
$k = $y - $m*$x;
$ans = "-$b/$a x + $k";

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Find an equation for the linear function \(g(x)\) which is perpendicular
to the line \( $a x - $b y = $c \) and intersects the line
\( $a x - $b y = $c \) at \( x = $x \).
$PAR
\( g(x) = \ \) \{ ans_rule(25) \}
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS( Compute($ans)->cmp() );

($n,$d) = reduce($a,$b);
$m1 = ( $d == 1 ) ? $n : "\frac{$n}{$d}";
($n,$d) = reduce($c,$b);
$b1 = ( $d == 1 ) ? $n : "\frac{$n}{$d}";
($n,$d) = reduce($b,$a);
$m2 = ( $d == 1 ) ? $n : "\frac{$n}{$d}";

($n,$d) = reduce($y*$a+$b*$x, $a);
$bk = ( $d == 1 ) ? $n : "\frac{$n}{$d}";

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR
$BBOLD SOLUTION $EBOLD
$PAR
First we place the line \( $a x - $b y = $c \) into slope-intercept form:
\[\begin{aligned}
 $a x - $b y &= $c \\
 $b y &= $a x - $c \\
  y &= $m1 x - $b1.
\end{aligned}\]
The slope of this line is \( m = $m1 \). Since the graph of
\(g(x)\) is perpendicular to it, the slope of \(g(x)\) is
\[ m = -\frac{1}{$m1} = - $m2 \]

$PAR
We see from the first equation that at \( x = $x \),
\[ y = $m1 ($x) - \frac{$c}{$b} = $y \]
so the graph of the first equation contains the point ($x, $y).
Since the graph of \(g(x)\) also contains this point, we have
\[ g($x) = b+ m($x) = $y, \]
or
\[ b + (-$m2) ($x) = $y \]
so
\[ b = $y + ($m2)($x) \]
and thus \( b = $bk \).  So \( g(x) = - $m2 x + $bk \).
$BR
END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


ENDDOCUMENT();
